rComments: She really deserves more 5.0 reviews. Super caring about students doing well, but you need to want it to. Happy to give extra help. Dont ditch class regularly unless you have circumstances that explain it (she will understand), otherwise she will call out students who are often late/dont attend/do homework. No easy As here, but very fulfilling!

Wang Laoshi is one of the kindest profs I've encountered at U of T. Her teaching style demands you step out of your comfort zone and participate in class but she's encouraging and understanding. She values respect in her classroom, but will respect her students in return. Very understanding of personal circumstances and incredibly helpful.
Wang Laoshi was the best EAS language course teacher I had. She's also really cute and brings snacks to class around Chinese New Year or things relevant to courses.

Professor Rupprecht (or Wang Laoshi) is an excellent Chinese prof. I've learnt Chinese most of my life and was always somewhat passive towards learning, but Wang Laoshi helped revitalise my interest in my second language. She's extremely helpful and if you wish to do summer abroad programs in Chinese she'll be happy to help!
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: Awesome prof. Although the class can be difficult at times she's super helpful and always willing to help your own bettering as a student. Highly recommend her Chinese classes!

A very respectable woman. Very enthusiastic and understanding of students with little to no knowledge of Mandarin Chinese. Test, quizzes and exam are fair and solid representations of your knowledge in that class, but they are not that easy. Truly cares about teaching, will extend office hours for you. A lovely woman who, my favourite prof by far.
Great professor. Very personable. You must work hard to succeed in this course.
